################################################################################
# MVP 1 — FOUNDATION & LANDING PAGE
# AI-Based Recruitment & Skill-Matching Platform
# Goal: Set up project structure + build public-facing landing page
################################################################################

## PHASE 1: Project Setup & Tech Stack Decision
☐ Confirmed frontend: React.js (Vite) + Tailwind CSS + SCSS + Material UI
[ ] Confirmed backend: Node.js + Express.js
[ ] Confirmed database: MongoDB (cloud: MongoDB Atlas free tier)
[ ] Confirmed AI/ML API provider: OpenAI (GPT-4o-mini) via openai npm package
[ ] Initialize Git repository with proper .gitignore
[ ] Set up separate frontend/ and backend/ folders (or monorepo)
[ ] Create .env.example with all required environment variable placeholders
[ ] Set up linting: ESLint + Prettier (frontend + backend)
[ ] Set up README.md with project overview and local setup instructions

## PHASE 2: Backend Foundation
[ ] Initialize backend project: `npm init -y` inside /backend
[ ] Install core dependencies:
    [ ] express
    [ ] cors, helmet, dotenv, morgan
    [ ] jsonwebtoken (JWT auth)
    [ ] bcryptjs (password hashing)
    [ ] mongoose (MongoDB ODM)
    [ ] express-validator (input validation)
    [ ] multer (file upload middleware)
    [ ] bull + ioredis (async job queue for AI tasks)
    [ ] openai (OpenAI Node.js SDK)
    [ ] nodemon (dev dependency)
[ ] Connect to MongoDB Atlas:
    [ ] Add MONGODB_URI to .env
    [ ] Create mongoose connection in /config/db.js
    [ ] Test connection on server start
[ ] Set up health-check route: GET /api/health → { status: "ok" }
[ ] Create base folder structure:
    [ ] /routes
    [ ] /controllers
    [ ] /models (Mongoose schemas)
    [ ] /middleware
    [ ] /services
    [ ] /utils
    [ ] /config
    [ ] /queues (Bull job queues)
[ ] Set up global error handling middleware
[ ] Set up request logging with morgan
[ ] Write initial Mongoose schemas: User, Job, Application, Resume

## PHASE 3: Frontend Foundation
[ ] Initialize React project: `npm create vite@latest frontend -- --template react`
[ ] Install core dependencies:
    [ ] react-router-dom (v6+)
    [ ] axios
    [ ] @tanstack/react-query (data fetching + caching)
    [ ] zustand (lightweight state management)
    [ ] @mui/material @mui/icons-material @emotion/react @emotion/styled (Material UI)
    [ ] tailwindcss postcss autoprefixer (Tailwind CSS)
    [ ] sass (SCSS support)
    [ ] react-hook-form + zod + @hookform/resolvers (form validation)
    [ ] react-dropzone (resume drag-and-drop upload)
    [ ] react-toastify (toast notifications)
    [ ] framer-motion (animations)
    [ ] dayjs (date formatting)
[ ] Configure Tailwind CSS:
    [ ] Run: `npx tailwindcss init -p`
    [ ] Add Tailwind directives to index.css
    [ ] Configure content paths in tailwind.config.js
[ ] Configure SCSS:
    [ ] Create /src/styles/_variables.scss, _mixins.scss, _globals.scss
    [ ] Import global SCSS in main.jsx
[ ] Configure Material UI theme:
    [ ] Create /src/theme/muiTheme.js with custom palette, typography
    [ ] Wrap App in <ThemeProvider>
[ ] Create base folder structure:
    [ ] /src/pages
    [ ] /src/components (shared UI components)
    [ ] /src/layouts
    [ ] /src/hooks
    [ ] /src/services (Axios API layer)
    [ ] /src/store (Zustand stores)
    [ ] /src/utils
    [ ] /src/styles (SCSS files)
    [ ] /src/theme (MUI theme config)
[ ] Set up react-router-dom with base routes:
    [ ] / → LandingPage
    [ ] /login → LoginPage
    [ ] /signup → SignupPage
    [ ] /dashboard/* → UserDashboard (protected)
    [ ] /recruiter/* → RecruiterDashboard (protected)
[ ] Create base Layout component (with Navbar + Footer)

