## PHASE 5: Domain & Hosting Setup
✔ Register domain (.com / .in / .tech): ₹1,900 (Namecheap recommended) @done(26-03-16 08:58)
[ ] Frontend deployment — Vercel:
    [ ] Push frontend/ folder to GitHub
    [ ] Connect GitHub repo to Vercel (vercel.com)
    [ ] Set root directory to frontend/ in Vercel settings
    [ ] Add env var: VITE_API_URL=https://your-api.onrender.com
    [ ] Add custom domain (yourdomain.com) in Vercel dashboard
[ ] Backend deployment — Render:
    [ ] Push backend/ folder to GitHub
    [ ] Create new "Web Service" on Render (render.com)
    [ ] Connect GitHub repo → select backend/ folder
    [ ] Build command: `npm install`
    [ ] Start command: `node server.js` OR `npm start`
    [ ] Add all environment variables in Render dashboard
    [ ] Add MongoDB Atlas connection string in env vars
    [ ] Enable auto-deploy on push to main branch
    [ ] Note: Render free tier spins down after 15 min inactivity (upgrade for always-on)
[ ] Set up CI/CD (GitHub Actions):
    [ ] Auto-deploy frontend to Vercel on push to main (Vercel GitHub integration)
    [ ] Auto-deploy backend to Render on push to main (Render GitHub integration)

## DELIVERABLES / ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA
[ ] Landing page renders correctly on all screen sizes
[ ] All nav sections scroll smoothly
[ ] "Apply" button for jobs redirects unauthenticated users to /login
[ ] Backend health-check endpoint returns 200 OK
[ ] Database connection established and tested
[ ] All environment variables documented in .env.example
[ ] Code pushed to Git repository
